08IFR_ruWR96K3Q6sakI_g
By far my favorite sushi in all of Phoenix.  High quality fish, mixed with a good atmosphere.  The proper mix of rice, veggies, and protein in the rolls.   They get very inventive with the specialty rolls and will accommodate anything you ask.   My wife doesn't always love sushi, so they have an "I hate sushi menu" that anyone can order off of.  Good happy hour deals and a staff that's been very long standing.   Anybody looking for great sushi should search out this little hidden gem.

